You are given a string S containing lowercase letters and digits. From S. extract all
maximal consecutive digit substrings and from these substrings form adjacent pairs.
For each pair (A.B) you have to compare:
The last digit of substring A with the first digit of substring B
Your task is to find and return an integer value representing the number of valid
adjacent digit substring pairs where the last digit of the first substring is not equal to
the first digit of the second.

Input Specification:
input1: A string S consisting of digits (0-9) and lowercase English letters (a-2)

Output Specification:
Return an integer value representing the number of valid adjacent digit substring
pairs where the last digit of the first substring is not equal to the first digit of the
second

Example 1:
input1: ab123cd45ef67gh8
Output: 3

// Java Code

import java.util.*;
public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
        String s = sc.next();
        ArrayList<String>List = new ArrayList<>();
        String temp = "";
        for(int i=0; i<s.length(); i++) {
            char ch = s.charAt(i);
            if(Character.isDigit(ch)) {
                temp += ch;
            }else {
                if(!temp.isEmpty()) {
                    List.add(temp);
                    temp = "";
                }
            }
        }
        if(!temp.isEmpty()) {
            List.add(temp);
        }
        int count = 0;
        for(int i =0; i<List.size()-1; i++) {
            char last = List.get(i).charAt(List.get(i).length()-1);
            char first = List.get(i + 1).charAt(0);
               if(last != first){
                    count++;
                }
        }
        System.out.println(count);
    }
}
